# ShieldReport Project Walkthrough

I have successfully architected and implemented the entire **ShieldReport: Speak Without Fear** web application based on your comprehensive project brief. 

This platform serves as a 100% anonymous, extremely secure, and AI-powered reporting system.

## 1. Security & Deep Anonymity Architecture
The most critical part of this application was ensuring absolute safety for the reporter.
*   **IP Stripping Middleware**: Found natively in `[ipStripper.ts](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/backend/src/middleware/ipStripper.ts)`, this executes before any routing logic. It forcefully overrides `/req.ip` and strips `x-forwarded-for` and `user-agent` to ensure that no metadata even has the chance of being recorded.
*   **Zero-Knowledge Authentication**: Instead of emails, the system issues a fully anonymous 12-character `CASE TOKEN` dynamically generated via base64 encoded cryptographic bytes.
*   **Data-at-Rest Encryption (AES-256-GCM)**: The actual plain text description is *never* stored. The `[encryption.ts](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/backend/src/utils/encryption.ts)` utility uses highly secure AES-256 algorithm to lock the description directly on the server before insertion into Prisma.

You can view the full architectural proof in `[anonymity.md](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/docs/anonymity.md)` and `[security.md](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/docs/security.md)`.

## 2. Advanced React PWA
The frontend codebase `[frontend/](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/frontend)` uses Vite, React, TailwindCSS, and Framer Motion built entirely around a custom Deep Navy and Shield Blue theme.
*   **Multi-Step Submission**: `[ReportForm.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/frontend/src/pages/ReportForm.tsx)` provides a stunning native-app feel with fluid step animations and constant reassurance regarding security.
*   **Landing Page**: Filled with visually distinct trust signals.
*   **Track Case Portal**: A secure terminal interface where users can type in their `CASE TOKEN` and instantly view the sanitized timeline of their report.

## 3. Real-Time AI Investigator Panel
The backend features an OpenAI GPT-4o pipeline linked directly to the ingestion route.
*   Located in `[aiAnalyzer.ts](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/backend/src/utils/aiAnalyzer.ts)`.
*   Before the incident report is encrypted and locked, the raw payload is sent to GPT-4o directly to generate an `urgencyScore`, a 2-line `summary`, and `tags`.
*   This data is fed into the `[Dashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hp/Downloads/ShieldReport/frontend/src/pages/admin/Dashboard.tsx)`, instantly allowing HR and Admin officials to spot `90+/100` critical severity cases.

